{"id":42,"parent_id":0,"book_id":22563,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":42,"title":"“Heirs of God, and Joint-heirs with Christ”","subtitle":"","short_title":40,"uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ","content":[["div",{"id":"head1","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.head1"},[".titleNumber","40"],["h1","“Heirs of God, and Joint-heirs with Christ”"]],[".bodyBlock",[".topic",["h2","Theme"],["div",{"id":"p4","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p4"},"Man’s highest potential is to become an heir to all that the Father has."]],[".topic",["h2","Theme Analysis"],["div",{"id":"f1","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f1"},["ul.content-list alphaCaps",["li",["span.label","A."],["div",[".para","Men and women are the spiritual offspring of God."],["div",{"id":"f2","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f2"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","We were born of eternal beings in the premortal world."]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","We, therefore, have the potential to become like our eternal parents."]]]]]],["li",["span.label","B."],["div",[".para","Man is also created in the physical image and likeness of God."]]],["li",["span.label","C."],["div",[".para","Through obedience to the gospel, men and women may become joint-heirs with the Savior to all that the Father has."],["div",{"id":"f3","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f3"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","Jesus, as the literal son of God, is the natural heir of his Father"]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","By heirship and by obedience Jesus attained to all that the Father has."]],["li",["span.label","3."],[".para","We can inherit equally with Christ all that the Father has by being obedient to the gospel."]]]]]]]]],[".topic",["h2","Study Sources"],[".topic",["h3","New Testament Reading Assignment"],["div",{"id":"p16","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p16"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/6"},"Romans 6-8"]]],[".topic",["h3","Course Manual"],["div",{"id":"p18","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p18"},"Chapter 40, “Heirs of God, and Joint-Heirs with Christ”"]],[".topic",["h3","Standard Works"],["div",{"id":"p20","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p20"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/12.48"},"3 Nephi 12:48"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/bofm/3-ne/27.27"},"27:27"],". What commandments are we given by the Lord?"],["div",{"id":"p21","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p21"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/philip/2.5,6"},"Philippians 2:5, 6"],"."],["div",{"id":"p22","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p22"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/17.2-6,15-22"},"John 17:2-6, 15-22"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.2-4,21-26"},"D&C 93:2-4, 21-26"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/heb/1.3,4"},"Hebrews 1:3, 4"],". What goal should we share in common with our Savior?"],["div",{"id":"p23","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p23"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/8.14-19"},"Romans 8:14-19"],". By what principles are men entitled to become heirs of God with their Redeemer?"],["div",{"id":"p24","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p24"},["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/pgp/moses/6.64-68"},"Moses 6:64-68"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.31-39"},"D&C 84:31-39"],". What else must we do to become heirs of God? D&C 93:11-20, 26-28. What promise is ours if we keep the commandments of God?"]],[".topic",["h3","Basic Library"],["div",{"id":"p26","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p26"},["span.emphasis","DS,"],"2:35-40. The doctrine of joint-heir ship."],["div",{"id":"p27","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p27"},["span.emphasis","Teachings,"],"p. 54. What must we do to become joint-heirs with the Savior?"],["div",{"id":"p28","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p28"},["span.emphasis","Teachings,"],"p. 347. What will be the glory of those who become joint-heirs with Jesus?"],["div",{"id":"p29","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p29"},["span.emphasis","Gos. Doc,"],"p. 18. How can we become the sons of God?"],["div",{"id":"p30","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p30"},["span.emphasis","Discourses,"],"pp. 96-97. What is man’s destiny?"]],[".topic",["h3","Additional Sources"],["div",{"id":"p32","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p32"},"Bruce R. McConkie,",["span.emphasis","Mormon Doctrine,"],"p. 394. A discussion of what it means to become a joint-heir."]]],[".topic",["h2","Some Suggestions for Presentation"],[".subtitle","(Ideas Other Teachers Have Used)"],[".topic",["h3","Man’s Ultimate Goal Is to Become Like God (A Discussion)"],["div",{"id":"p36","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p36"},"The teacher could ask his students to consider what their ultimate goals are, both in this life and in the life to come."],["div",{"id":"p37","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p37"},"Is it really possible for us to become like God? If so, what do we know about God? What is He like? (He is perfect; he completely obeys the law of a celestial glory.) What, then, should be our goal? (The teacher might wish to discuss item 40-6 with the students.)"]],[".topic",["h3","We Can Become Heirs of God (A Discussion)"],["div",{"id":"p39","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p39"},"The teacher could write on the board the title of this lesson, “Heirs of God, and Joint-Heirs with Christ” (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/8.17"},"Romans 8:17"],"), and hold a discussion on the meaning of the word",["span.emphasis","heir."]],["div",{"id":"p40","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p40"},"Heirship of the world and heirship of eternal blessings could be contrasted. (See item 40-8.)"]],[".topic",["h3","An Heir of Worldly Things"]],[".topic",["h3","An Heir of God"],["div",{"id":"f4","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f4"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","Receives property, money, titles, and the like."]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","Is entitled, generally, to the inheritance because of birth."]],["li",["span.label","3."],[".para","Others."]]]],["div",{"id":"f5","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f5"},["ol.number",["li",["span.label","1."],[".para","Receives all that the Father has."]],["li",["span.label","2."],[".para","Is entitled to this inheritance by qualifying for the prounounced blessings."]],["li",["span.label","3."],[".para","Others."]]]]],[".topic",["h3","How Do We Become Heirs of God? (Chalkboard Illustration and Scripture Analysis)"],["div",{"id":"p50","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p50"},"The following scriptures could be used to teach the concept that we become heirs of God through Jesus Christ. (See item 40-9.)"],["div",{"id":"p51","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p51"},"Was a natural heir to all that the Father has, but earned the right to his inheritance through obedience"],[".",{"id":"f6","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f6"}],["div",{"id":"p55","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.p55"},"By complete obedience to the gospel, we gain our inheritance through Jesus Christ and his grace and love."],["div",{"id":"f7","uri":"/manual/the-life-and-teachings-of-jesus-and-his-apostles-instructors-guide-rel-211-12/heirs-of-god-and-joint-heirs-with-christ.f7"},["table",["tbody",["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/john/16.15"},"John 16:15"]]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","Because Jesus was the son of God, to what was he a natural heir?"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.5-17"},"D&C 93:5-17"]]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","How did Jesus attain unto a fulness of what his Father possessed?"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/rom/8.14-18"},"Romans 8:14-18"]]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","How do we become “joint-heirs”?"]]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/3.26-29"},"Galatians 3:26-29"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/4.1-7"},"4:1-7"]]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"}]],["tr",["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/84.33-41"},"D&C 84:33-41"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/50.26-28"},"50:26-28"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/76.50-60"},"76:50-60"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/88.107"},"88:107"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/93.15-30"},"93:15-30"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/132.20"},"132:20"]]],["td",{"colspan":"1","rowspan":"1"},[".para","As joint-heirs with the Savior, what blessings can we receive from the Father?"]]]]]]]]]],"refs":null}
